title: Wulf the Barbarian # 1-4 (Atlas Comics)
description:
A comic book that never surpassed four issues and ends pretty abrubtly, but Klaus Janson and Larry Hama worked on it.

Note: This is not published by the same Atlas that would turn into Marvel. Atlas Comics was a small publisher that lasted less than a year in the mid-70's, but still managed to publish a impressive volume of books and attracted notable creators like Neal Adams, Steve Ditko and Wally Wood.
